properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 8 at 2:05PM CST until February 10 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...PERIOD OF STRONG GUSTY WINDS EXPECTED SUNDAY AND SUNDAY
NIGHT...

* WHAT...Southwest winds increasing to 15 to 25 knots Sunday
morning with gusts up to 30 knots. Waves building to 3 to 6 feet
with the highest winds well offshore.

* WHERE...Nearshore waters from Sheboygan to Winthrop Harbor IL.

* WHEN...From 9 AM Sunday to 3 AM CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM SUNDAY TO 3 AM CST MONDAY
